@1474 = ~Diriel, I'm not trying to push you away, but I'd like a bit less attention. Perhaps, if we stop flirting, it would be better.~
@1475 = ~(His palm is narrow, his fingers elegant and flawlessly trimmed. A few faint alchemical stains are visible on the even, warmly-colored skin, a testimony to years of grinding herbs and mixing draughts.)~
@1476 = ~Do not move away immediately. Studying your touch is of great interest to me.~
@1477 = ~I believe that I am capable of recognizing your hand's touch without error by its ability to cause my skin to... to burn for the lack of a better term.~
@1478 = ~I previously considered the linking of hands vulgar and unnecessary, however this experience makes me reconsider my position.~
@1479 = ~(The tresses fall back over his eyes. He jerks his head to send them flying away.)~
@1480 = ~(A dusting of snow remains, adding sparkles to his hair, like jewels in the silver hairnets of courtiers.)~
@1481 = ~(His hair shines as brightly in the sunlight as the snow.)~
@1482 = ~(Some of the dark-golden locks are frozen together.)~
