@1503 = ~(Lean over his hand and drink from it.) ~
@1504 = ~(Slap his hand away, flinging the water into his face.)~
@1505 = ~I welcome the show of pride, but not the waste of our resources. Always think of survival first.~
@1506 = ~(His hands and the water smells of pine needles.)~
@1507 = ~(His palm visibly trembles when your lips touch the water.)~
@1508 = ~(He looks very surprised when you lift your head up. Surprised and maybe moved.)~
@1509 = ~I expected you to say that. A proud elf drinks out of no palm but her own. (He gives you his water skin without further comment.)~
@1510 = ~Under other circumstances water would be considered a gift of life, <CHARNAME>.  Here we do not lack it due to snow coverage. However, learning to preserve your water store and finding water sources is important.~
@1511 = ~I shall make a note of teaching you about it.~
@1512 = ~(Without a word he extends his water skin to you, but he watches you drink rather more intently than you'd expect.)~
@1513 = ~A snow quail attempting to impress his potential mate.~
@1514 = ~Then I shall endeavor to alert you, should I spot the event.~
@1515 = ~Indeed we shall proceed.~
@1516 = ~You did?	~
@1517 = ~The strongest wins and breeds, <CHARNAME>. That is how this world is made.~
@1518 = ~Quite so, for how could rivals stand up to the one who is a perfect match?~
@1519 = ~Only if the perfect match does not present itself,  <CHARNAME>.~
@1520 = ~Indeed, for how could rivals measure up to the one who is a perfect match?~
@1521 = ~You are wise to test me. You shall need my ability ere our journey is done.~
@1522 = ~You cannot be unaware of the fact that it is the right season for us to see the mating dances of this particular species; in all probability we will witness it sooner or later.~
@1523 = ~I think this particular bird succeeded. Do you agree?~
@1524 = ~I would love to do it in your company. ~
@1525 = ~Well, all right, let's go.~
@1526 = ~You shall need my ability ere our journey is done.~
@1527 = ~There is a high probability that we shall witness their mating dances. It is the right season for it.~
@1528 = ~So, did... did he succeed? The bird?~
@1529 = ~Eventually. There was a rival.~
@1530 = ~Truly? That is so similar to... nevermind.~
@1531 = ~A bit of rivalry is stimulating sometimes.~
@1532 = ~But he was beaten thoroughly? ~
@1533 = ~By whatever reason I am glad that this particular bird won the one he coveted. ~
@1534 = ~Oh, I hoped it would lose. ~
@1535 = ~Surely you can read it yourself? It is a very distinctive pattern. Here is the wing brushing the snow, the feather prints, the beak print as it dipped its neck... the footprints... step... step...~
@1536 = ~Did... did he succeed?~
@1537 = ~(Smile.) I can nigh see it. ~
@1538 = ~All right, I am convinced - you can do it.~
@1539 = ~It is a very distinctive pattern. Here is the wing brushing the snow, the feather prints, the beak print as it dipped its neck... the footprints... step... step...~
@1540 = ~Thank you for reading them for me. I can nigh see it. ~
@1541 = ~All right, you can do it. That's enough tracking. ~
@1542 = ~I perceive that you are glad to have me traveling with you. The feeling is mutual.~
@1543 = ~You have an enigmatic smile, <CHARNAME>. It brings to mind a number of appropriately romantic recitations that prove the everlasting lure of that which is yet unknown.~
@1544 = ~(He smiles back politely, showing even, very white teeth.)~
@1545 = ~I am overjoyed that you are in a cheerful mood, <CHARNAME>.~
@1546 = ~Do you experience an episode of unhappiness?~
@1547 = ~No. Actually I am quite happy.~
@1548 = ~Can't I do anything without you commenting on it?~
@1549 = ~I am.~
@1550 = ~I don't know. It's a strange, elusive thing. I am not exactly happy, but neither I am unhappy. I think I may even like it. ~
@1551 = ~I am tired, that is all.~
@1552 = ~(Diriel looks at you without a shade of understanding in his eyes. After a moments hesitation he nods curtly and... sighs.)~
@1553 = ~A cup of chamomile tea will help restore and balance your spirit. I shall brew it for you once we stop to break our fast.~
@1554 = ~If I could come up with a sufficiently comic topic, I would have done so. Alas, I do not make light of my cause, and I have no interest in speaking of banalities in the face of the elvendom's crisis.~
@1555 = ~While I do not condone perpetual cheerfulness, somber moods can lead to dangerous consequences in our kin of late, such as Retreat. You must attempt to... ahem... cheer up.~
@1556 = ~Then I erred in thinking that it was done on my behalf. I apologize.~
@1557 = ~Reading emotions is not my strong suit. However, if you need me to tell you of the landscape or animal tracks, I am at your disposal.~
@1558 = ~I deduce that you take pleasure in puzzling me.~
@1559 = ~Sighs are deceptive.~
@1560 = ~(By a coincidence, Diriel is glancing at you.)~
@1561 = ~(Share a knowing look.)~
@1562 = ~(You press your palms against your blushing cheeks.)~
@1563 = ~(Lower your eyes.)~
@1564 = ~(You see the tips of Diriel's boots as he noiselessly comes close to you... then they retreat.)~
@1565 = ~(When you look up, Diriel is attending to his duties.)~
@1566 = ~(And so you do not see him crossing the distance between you before he firmly touches your hand.)~
@1567 = ~I do not think that anything is wrong, however if there is... you can tell me.~
@1568 = ~I would have asked you to discontinue this, however blushing is involuntary. I wish it were less unnerving.~
@1569 = ~You are blushing. My appearance is not hideous or improper. I do not understa- (Diriel never finishes the sentence, suddenly blushing himself.)~
@1570 = ~If you are feverish, I can prepare some willow bark tea.~
@1571 = ~(Your silent exchange visibly pleases Diriel.)~
@1572 = ~I am glad to have encountered someone as perceptive as you are. (A co-conspirator's smile curves his lips.)~
@1573 = ~(Diriel nods sagely.) Precisely.~
@1574 = ~<CHARNAME>, I assure you I am quite proficient in this exercise, having observed the Great Mother's many creatures. (He gives you a lecherous look that puts your efforts to shame.)~
@1575 = ~You are neither a human, nor are you at a slave market. This is unbecoming to you.~
@1576 = ~I have not noticed many elven men in Luskan, and certainly none that compare to me, however I did not suspect that it affected you so much. This goes to prove yet another time that no elf should be raised among humans.~
@1577 = ~(Diriel shrugs and ignores you.)~
@1578 = ~Not many would call me a man of passion, however, I am certainly skillful.~
@1579 = ~I am pleased that it is you who are our commander, not your father's despicable... associate.~
@1580 = ~You showed keen wisdom in recruiting me.~
@1581 = ~Indeed.~
@1582 = ~Thank you.~
@1583 = ~And you are a very attractive woman, <CHARNAME>.~
@1584 = ~It is something that has been noted on a several occasions previously.~
@1585 = ~None and each of them. ~
@1586 = ~I have a better knowledge of the animals whose form I can take. Hence I wish to learn as many forms as I can. The world's infinite variety fascinates me. ~
@1587 = ~I am a druid, not a babe who queries his parents for a pet. ~
@1588 = ~There could be no definitive answer to this question. ~
@1589 = ~I question your sincerity, because you surround yourself with the enemy.~
@1590 = ~The progress is slow, however I have had much time for planning and preparation. Once the war is unleashed, it must be swift, to exterminate the parasites before they adapt and multiply.~
@1591 = ~You shall be notified of my successes by the diminishing of the stench in the air.~
@1592 = ~In this region I am pitted by necessity against the least obnoxious kind of humans - the barbarians.~
@1593 = ~(Diriel gives you an injured look and doesn't deign to reply.)~
@1594 = ~Do you require anything, my love?~
@1595 = ~(You hug Diriel.)~
@1596 = ~(Throw a smoldering glance Diriel's way.)~
@1597 = ~(Slide your fingers into Diriel’s blond mane.)~
@1598 = ~(You slap Diriel’s bottom.)~
@1599 = ~This climate is conductive to sharing warmth with someone, don't you find?~
@1600 = ~My lips keep getting so dry here!~
@1601 = ~Diriel, I am curious about your writing. You always scribble notes in your diary. What they are about?~
@1602 = ~(Tickle Diriel.)~
@1603 = ~(Stick your tongue out at Diriel.)~
@1604 = ~(You found a dried daisy flower in Diriel's medicinal bag.) 'He loves me...' 'He loves me not...' ~
@1605 = ~(Nestle close to Diriel.)~
@1606 = ~(Kiss Diriel on the lips.)~
@1607 = ~(Kiss Diriel's eyes.)~
@1608 = ~(Lean on Diriel.)~
@1609 = ~(Bite Diriel.)~
@1610 = ~Diriel, I have done some thinking, and I believe that our engagement was a mistake. I do not want to marry you.~
@1611 = ~(Diriel arches his golden eyebrow questioningly.)  Are you going feral already?~
@1612 = ~If you are hungry, dear heart, whatever the nature of your hunger, I can satiate you if we break for a while. ~
@1613 = ~(Disregarding anything and anyone around, Diriel draws you closer to him and nibbles at your neck.) I miss you. ~
@1614 = ~(He lifts his hand slowly and touches the corner of your mouth with the tips of two fingers.) ~
@1615 = ~I have been bitten many times, and I appreciate it that I do not need to draw poison from the wound this time. Or that it is indeed not a wound at all for that matter. And that you passion for me takes requires such dramatic form to express itself.~
@1616 = ~(He inhales deeply of your smell and kisses your hair.) ~
@1617 = ~Stay here until I count out ten heartbeats. One... ~
@1618 = ~Two...~
@1619 = ~(The interval shortens.) Three...~
@1620 = ~Alas, they are not as precise a measurement of time's passing as they used to be. My heart beats considerably faster when you are this close.~
@1621 = ~(As soon as your back touches his chest, he wraps his arms around your waist putting a protective palm on your stomach.)~
@1622 = ~My beautiful fiancée, I am overjoyed by the symbolism of this gesture. You are as willing to accept my protection, as I am willing to provide it.~
@1623 = ~You are exceedingly creative in suggesting new ways in which the lovers can kiss.~
@1624 = ~(He kisses the corner of your eye.)~
@1625 = ~(He closes his eyes as he guesses your intentions and stands very still, infinitely attentive to the every little detail of the kiss.)~
@1626 = ~My beautiful fiancée, I am blinded by you as is. (An embarrassed smile curves his lips.)~
@1627 = ~I... attempted a joke. It was an unfortunate idea.~
@1628 = ~(Bright and sharp blue, Diriel's eyes sometimes seems to be an object of art, a heirloom... even more so when he looks at you, and his glance warms up.) ~
@1629 = ~Each kiss is a journey. (He nods to himself; it's likely that a detailed case study will appear in his journal later in the day.)~
@1630 = ~Counting this kiss, the grand total of our kisses is.... (he presses his lips back to yours.) ~
@1631 = ~(Sigh.) I believe that it can be expressed as 'n plus one' at any given time.~
@1632 = ~I was anticipating this, however I was taken by surprise. There is no end to the contradictions in love.~
@1633 = ~This experience could potentially break my composure, <CHARNAME>.~
@1634 = ~And then you'll ravage me?~
@1635 = ~We can't have that. A pity, really. I do like kissing you once in a while.~
@1636 = ~(Laugh and kiss him again.)~
@1637 = ~I... I am sorry.~
@1638 = ~(Diriel taps his chin thoughtfully.) Very probably.~
@1639 = ~(Diriel seals your lips with a kiss of his own.) If we observe certain interval... in between... we might successfully kiss without causing any explosions.~
@1640 = ~You appeal to my primeval instincts in an unerring fashion, therefore managing to control the incontrollable. I wish I could document this, however I am always prevented from doing it by the need to confirm one detail or another, and once the experiment is under way, it cannot be interrupted.~
@1641 = ~As am I, however, we are both working towards constructing the environment where our kissing and the consequences thereof can be conducted safely.~
@1642 = ~(Diriel presses his cheek against the side of your forehead.) Quite soon we shall conquer this world and then time will be ours to spend as we please.~
@1643 = ~(He wraps his arm around your waist and murmurs into your ear.) Do not overburden your mind with worry. I am standing guard for you.~
@1644 = ~(Diriel strokes your hair.) How very similar it is to all others', and how very different, how very superior.~
@1645 = ~(He throws his cloak around you, so you both are wrapped in it.)~
@1646 = ~He loves you, however he asks you to keep away from his herbs, for he knows not when the need may arise for a particular draught.~
@1647 = ~I would have used a live flower if there were any!~
@1648 = ~Ah, how very presumptuous of you to think that I meant you.~
@1649 = ~Please, don't get cross. I'll keep out of your satchel. ~
@1650 = ~Don't worry, you have plenty of daisies there. ~
@1651 = ~'He loves me...'~
@1652 = ~Then I will leave you to your thoughts. It appears that you have a lot of thinking to do.~
@1653 = ~(Diriel takes the dried flower away from you and returns it to the pouch.)~
@1654 = ~I will ask you to be honorable and break our engagement.~
@1655 = ~Then consider acting as befits my fiancée.~
@1656 = ~Their pungency is irrelevant; their efficiency is unquestionable.~
@1657 = ~I have conducted some research and this was suggested as a method of terminating these out of control discussions.~
@1658 = ~(Diriel kisses you.)~
@1659 = ~I suspect that it is due to the fact these flowers tend to have an odd number of petals, and you are of the opinion that most men fall for you the moment they lay their eyes on you. Please, return the flower into the pouch, and let us continue on.~
@1660 = ~(Diriel sighs and holds the bag to gather the falling petals. Needless to say that the very last petal left on the flower is the 'He loves me' one.)~
@1661 = ~Are you satisfied with the result?~
@1662 = ~Yes! (You try to pin what's left of the flower to your cloak.)~
@1663 = ~Yes! (You try to put what's left of the flower into his hair.) ~
@1664 = ~(Tease) No!~
@1665 = ~(Serious) No.~
@1666 = ~(Diriel cringes.) The quantity is irrelevant. Live flowers should not be harvested to be used in this highly inaccurate method of gathering data on others' feelings.~
@1667 = ~Inaccurate?! It never failed me before.~
@1668 = ~Ah, my love, you are so easy to tease!~
@1669 = ~Yes, yes. It's glorious destiny is to be turned into one of your pungent draughts.~
@1670 = ~Don't you scold me; I'm your wife to be, not a servant.~
@1671 = ~I shall be most grateful if you will. No flower should be harvested to be used in this highly inaccurate method of gathering data on others' feelings.~
@1672 = ~It is not a presumption, but a deduction based on the fact that we are engaged to be married. I will not suffer you destroying my herbal stock while day-dreaming about a perpetrator.~
@1673 = ~And what will you do if it was someone else? ~
@1674 = ~(Diriel cringes.) No, this was not what I tried to imprint on you. Live flowers should not be harvested to be used in this highly inaccurate method of gathering data on others' feelings.~
@1675 = ~I urge you not to make this decision lightly. Our son and our cause will benefit greatly from this union.~
@1676 = ~Yes, and that is why I do not want to marry you. It's all about the cause....~
@1677 = ~I do not want this child either, Diriel. You promised me the herbs. I want them before it is too late.~
@1678 = ~I did not arrive to this decision lightly. But I do not love you, and I do not want to marry you.~
@1679 = ~I suppose so. Ah, Diriel, you have truly trapped me. ~
@1680 = ~I told you the truth. I will not harm you.~
@1681 = ~I do not. I will not harm you.~
@1682 = ~I am glad that you have come to this conclusion.~
@1683 = ~I can neither force nor convince you to love me. It is resolved then, if not to my satisfaction.~
@1684 = ~It is too late.~
@1685 = ~You lie!~
@1686 = ~Well, there are ways to deal with our relationship without harming the child.~
@1687 = ~Oh, really? I promise you that you will not come within a league from him, even if he is born. ~
@1688 = ~I suppose so. Ah, Diriel, you truly trapped me. ~
@1689 = ~I love you. I do not know how I can prove it to you, but I love you.~
@1690 = ~I... I believe you. I should not have doubted you.~
@1691 = ~It is not enough. I am sorry, Diriel, but our engagement is over. ~
@1692 = ~And I am to believe that these words are not calculated? You have a stone in place of a heart, and I am not going to suffer it through my entire life. ~
@1693 = ~I don't care, because I do not love you. ~
@1694 = ~(He cocks his head to one shoulder surveying the view.) I do not think it makes you more attractive.~
@1695 = ~Place your tongue where it belongs before it starts freezing in this position.~
@1696 = ~I suggest that you repeat this action when our lips are pressed against each other's in a kiss.~
@1697 = ~I see no abnormalities in the appearance of your tongue, <CHARNAME>.~
@1698 = ~(He tickles your neck...~
@1699 = ~(...with his tongue.)~
@1700 = ~An improvement, yes.~
@1701 = ~If I were shapeshifted into a feline, and you tickled my ears or chin... would I purr?~
@1702 = ~Clothes and amour greatly reduce the effectiveness of the procedure. Therefore, you would be more successful when we are without.~
@1703 = ~(Diriel stoically allows you to tickle him to your heart's content without making a single move.)~
@1704 = ~The last thing I have recorded was a... a poem. I will not have you suffer through its recitation.~
@1705 = ~Instead, I am resolved to purchase a compilation of classic texts. At the very least they will serve to educate you in the ways of our culture, unlike modern diatribes.~
@1706 = ~They are comprised of the useful data I collect, though I have noticed that I have penned a few frivolous ideas as well. Perhaps, it is time for me to start keeping two journals.~
@1707 = ~Every fact worthy of recording, categorizing and preserving for future research.~
@1708 = ~As of lately, I have been making a lot of observations on one woman, love and passion.~
@1709 = ~Let me examine the damaged tissues... (Diriel cups your chin and moves your head from left to right to better survey your lips.)~
@1710 = ~My beautiful fiancée, your lips are as perfect as the rest of you. They are the thing of magic, so teasing and mesmerizing, a gateway to your thoughts, an embodiment of a kiss.~
@1711 = ~Do not bite them, my love, drink plenty and the damage should heal.~
@1712 = ~They are... still? You are not adapting well to the climate, and this is worrisome. We need to accelerate the process of acquiring our kingdom, so we can create proper conditions for your gentle skin.~
@1713 = ~Halt then. (Diriel produces an ointment from his pouch.)~
@1714 = ~Here is a substance that might help. (He applies a liberal portion of sticky substance to your chapped lips. You can taste something sweet... perhaps strawberries?)~
@1715 = ~I have a foolhardy theory that frequent administering of this... (kiss) ... will keep them moist.~
@1716 = ~Specify the type of warmth to be shared. Is it bodily warmth? The warmth created by combusting wood or coal?~
@1717 = ~The warmth of one's beloved's smile, however scientifically unproven this particular source of heat may be?~
@1718 = ~This hypothesis is asking to be tested. (Diriel embraces you, pressing his cheek against yours.)~
@1719 = ~Bodily warmth is indeed an engaging concept.~
@1720 = ~I trust that you did not mean 'anyone', but rather someone who shares a special relationship with you. Someone like me.~
@1721 = ~We are elves, <CHARNAME>, one of our supreme qualities is that we are at ease with the elements.~
@1722 = ~However, we can experience the feeling of comfort that close proximity to a desirable representative of the same species creates.~
@1723 = ~(You hear a satisfying clap as your palm connects with the druid's hind parts and an unexpected squeal.) ~
@1724 = ~I have read about a certain species in Chult that has a thick hide, almost akin to metal plating. At times I entertain the thought of studying them further and shapeshifting into one.~
@1725 = ~I would prefer you do this when we have more privacy. ~
@1726 = ~I absolutely must to conduct an experiment to determine the attraction this particular action holds for you.~
@1727 = ~(Diriel gives you a smack below the waste.) Oh. I am starting to understand... (He manages a decent squeeze.)~
@1728 = ~It does not need the compaction. (Indeed, it is quite tight, if not precisely bony.)~
@1729 = ~(There is a familiar smell to his hair, of freezing leaves and autumnal herbs, slightly bitter, slightly cool, but made sharper and brighter by the frost.)~
@1730 = ~(You find a thick lock glued together by dried blood. The skin of his scalp is broken underneath.)~
@1731 = ~(Diriel winces and mumbles, without looking at his feet.) ...when there is no more efficient use for my healing....~
@1732 = ~(The thick, heavy hair parts as you path your fingers through it only to watch it close immediately behind; almost like water in a stream, if water can be golden.)~
@1733 = ~(Diriel leans his head back, his eyes closed with pleasure.) Mmgh... I love your tender digits.~
@1734 = ~You are impeding our progress, <CHARNAME>. I require an interval of time to regain the ability to think clearly.~
@1735 = ~You are challenging me to unleash a glance that I designed to make you melt. However, I prefer to save it for now.~
@1736 = ~(He stretches in a lazy, content fashion.)~
@1737 = ~(Diriel covers his eyes with his palm as if shielding himself from a bright light, then smiles and moves his hand up a bit to see if you are still looking his way.)~
@1738 = ~(Diriel presses you against his chest with uncharacteristic impulsiveness. Then he swirls you around, laughing. When he finally stands you back on the ground, there is a small self-ironic smile on his face.)~
@1739 = ~Indeed....~
@1740 = ~(He strokes your back; he seems particular to its lower reaches.)~
@1741 = ~(He pushes hair out of your eyes and kisses you.) We must disengage this embrace now. ~
@1742 = ~(Smile widely and shake your head negatively.)~
@1743 = ~What if I don't want to? ~
@1744 = ~That was a nice kiss!~
@1745 = ~I return to thee thy freedom! ~
@1746 = ~All right. ~
@1747 = ~Yet, I am still enthralled. Such are the puzzling realities of love.~
@1748 = ~It complimented the embrace you have given me.~
@1749 = ~We shall repeat this at the first opportunity.~
@1750 = ~You are endangering us all. However, I find it difficult to care.~
@1751 = ~(Diriel slowly embraces you, his arms encircling your shoulders with astounding care.)~
@1752 = ~I am sorry that I wasn't a man enough to save you from the cage of hatred your 'true love' is locking you in.~
@1753 = ~I understand, Mistress. You don't want me for your consort.~
@1754 = ~Rizdaer, I decided that I am ready to have a lover. I want us to make love... or whatever you call it in drow.~
@1755 = ~Those are the sweetest words I've ever heard.~
@1756 = ~And yet again I'm dizzy, and I don't care if it is a surfacer's love or a drow's ssinssrigg. You know, I have not ever craved a female day after day, night after night before I met you. And I doubt that I will ever stop now.~
